data.enText: a thing that shows that sth else exists or is true

data.chText: 这种新型产品显示了全体员工的技术水平和敬业精神。
data.enText: The new model is a testament to the skill and dedication of the workforce.
This is the last will and testament of…

tr: a legal document declaring a person's wishes regarding the disposal of their property when they die

example: his easy victory was a testament to his skill

value.def: If one thing is a testament to another, it shows that the other thing exists or is true.

example.ex: Braka's house, just off Sloane Square, is a testament to his Gothic tastes...
example.tran: 布拉卡那幢紧靠斯隆广场的房子是他喜好哥特式建筑的一个证据。

example.ex: The fact that these scandals are now public is testament to the relative openness of America's government.
example.tran: 这些丑闻如今公之于众的事实说明了美国政府的相对透明。

value.def: Someone's last will and testament is the most recent will that they have made, especially the last will that they make before they die.
value.tran: 最新遗嘱;（尤指）临终遗嘱,临终遗言
